item.description: Biography I am a Master student in the Department of Mechanical and Mechatronics Engineering at University of Waterloo. Currently, I am working towards my Master’s thesis on Real Gas Effects on Compressible flows in Supercritical regime in Multiphysics Interation lab under the supervision of Professor Jean-Pierre Hickey. I opened this website to keep track of my graduate research life, academic courses, and last but not the least, ideas that I want to share with others.

item.title: Teaching
item.description: I work as a teaching assistant for the following courses of Mechanical and Mechatronics Engineering at University of Waterloo. I’ve taught tutorials and held office hours with students. ME 201: Advanced Calculus: Partial differential Equations, Vector Calculus ME 303: Advanced Engineering Mathematics: Computational methods for Ordinary, Partial differental equations
